#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""scry — local "Fusion" over headless AI CLIs.

Replicates OpenRouter's Fusion (a Mixture-of-Agents pipeline) without OpenRouter
and without API keys: it fans a prompt out to several models running through their
*subscription* CLIs in headless mode, then deliberates + synthesizes one answer.

Pipeline (mirrors OpenRouter Fusion):
  1. PANEL      — every configured proposer answers the prompt in parallel, each
                  with web_search + web_fetch enabled (Fusion behavior).
  2. JUDGE      — (mode=fusion) one model, also web-enabled, compares the answers
                  and emits a 5-field JSON analysis (consensus / contradictions /
                  partial_coverage / unique_insights / blind_spots) — it compares,
                  it does not merge.
  3. SYNTHESIS  — one aggregator model (no web tools, per Fusion) writes the final
                  answer (Mixture-of-Agents "Aggregate-and-Synthesize" prompt,
                  arXiv:2406.04692).

The only intended differences from real Fusion are (a) which models sit in the
panel and (b) the internal prompts (OpenRouter's are unpublished; we use the
canonical MoA aggregator + a reconstructed judge). Everything else — parallel
panel, web tools on panel+judge, judge=outer model, max_tool_calls cap, reasoning
effort, the 5-field analysis, and the {status, analysis, responses} output shape —
is matched. See README.md.

Zero dependencies: standard library only, runs on Python 3.9+ (system python3).
"""
